# .trivyignore -- deliberate, justified suppressions for `make trivy`
# (trivy fs --scanners vuln,secret,misconfig, see mk/security.mk).
#
# Only rules that genuinely do not apply to this repo's images are listed.
# Each entry records WHY. Reviewed 2026-06-07. Anything fixable in the
# Dockerfiles was fixed rather than suppressed (root user, RUN cd, busybox tag).

# AVD-DS-0026 -- "Add HEALTHCHECK instruction in your Dockerfile"
# Every image here is an interactive dev shell or a one-shot build/packaging
# stage -- none is a long-running service an orchestrator would probe, so a
# HEALTHCHECK would be inert. Not applicable.
AVD-DS-0026

# AVD-DS-0001 -- "Specify a tag in the 'FROM' statement"
# Remaining hits are intra-pipeline parents (apex.base, apex.dev.cpu,
# apex.dev.cuda) referenced by the :latest tag this repo's own Docker Images
# workflow builds and pushes; there is no upstream version/digest to pin. The
# only external base (busybox) IS pinned -- see docker/final.Dockerfile.
AVD-DS-0001

# AVD-DS-0014 -- "Shouldn't use both curl and wget"
# docker/base.Dockerfile intentionally ships both: downstream toolchain
# installers (TI, Espressif, Zephyr, vendor scripts) each hard-code one or the
# other. Stylistic (LOW); diverging would break installer expectations.
AVD-DS-0014
